{
  "stem": "7238.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she wanted to join us, but she was in Austria through the Zionist organization, looking for ways to put people in contact with families.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we paid a smuggler, who brought them over, and then she was already in Zeilsheim, living with us for a short while.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Since my brother-in-law had family in the United States, he got the priority [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] papers, and one day they left for the United States.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We couldn't go because this was the time of the McCarthy era, when all those who are born behind the Iron Curtain are communists, so they are not well-seen in the United States.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We cannot go.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We registered to go to join my sister, but it stopped.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And now a situation where I cannot live between the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I cannot go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then I go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we started to get organized to go to Marseilles to board a ship to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Our journey was not at the end at this time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "A little boat that fishermen used in Panama was rented by the then-Israeli government, because they didn't have money.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was already '48, after the declaration of Israel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they loaded in that small boat that could take only 200 people-- they loaded a thousand.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was very poorly equipped, and the first night, we have no motor going, and we are sinking.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A big storm hit us, and overnight we sent SOS to help us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With us, it was only one representative from Jerusalem to take care of us, to bring us over.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were ready to lynch this guy if he will not help us, because they were mothers with children who survived in the forests.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
